{
  "texts": [
    "Although providers currently bear much of the liability for AI malpractice, patients face risks to their health, privacy, and dignity.",
    "As medical AI becomes more prevalent, both patients and clinicians must educate themselves about its development and associated risks 48.",
    "AI vendors must also ensure transparency, enabling end-users to understand and critically evaluate the decisions made by these models 50.",
    "In 2022, the Department of Health and Human Services proposed extending the Affordable Care Act to include protections against biases in clinical algorithms.",
    "While this initiative aims to combat disparities, it has raised concerns about placing an unfair burden on healthcare professionals, requiring them to assess the fairness and legality of algorithms-tasks that often exceed their expertise 52, 53."
  ]
}